    "comment_regular_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "> With this approach, how would the code in https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/38744 look?\r\n\r\n```lua\r\nlocal archive_patterns = {\r\n  ['tar.gz'] = 'tar',\r\n  ['tar.bz2'] = 'tar',\r\n  ['tar.xz'] = 'tar',\r\n  ['txz'] = 'tar',\r\n  ['tar'] = 'tar',\r\n  ['zip'] = 'zip',\r\n}\r\n\r\n---@param url string\r\n---@return 'zip'|'tar'?\r\nlocal function archive_type(url)\r\n  local path = url_path(url)\r\n  local exts = vim.fs.ext(path, { max = 2 })\r\n  local last_ext = exts:gsub('.*%.', '')\r\n  return archive_patterns[exts] or archive_patterns[last_ext]\r\nend\r\n```\r\n\r\nOther options for the `last_ext` line include:\r\n1. `local last_ext = vim.fs.ext(path)`\r\n2. `local last_ext = vim.iter(vim.gsplit(exts, '.', { plain = true })):last()`\r\n3. `exts = vim.split(exts, '.', { plain = true }); local last_ext = exts[#exts]`",
