        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "If using `exts:gsub('.*%.', '')` then it feels like you might as well have used `gsub()` and skipped `vim.fs.ext()` entirely. Right? \r\n\r\nIs there any reason *not* to return multival with `max=n` ? The first retval could be the \"longest\" one, if that's more intuitive.",
